  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (stale requirement binding)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing requirement document is cited as ASME V&V 40-2018; however, the model baseline reflects a 2026-Q1 solver platform update and revised hemolysis power-law coefficients published in the 2023 addendum to ISO 10993-17, neither of which are acknowledged in the requirement binding.",
