      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MRL 2 requires Gradation 2: systematic mesh refinement study with quantified convergence metric for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed on volume-averaged shear stress and peak shear stress location across three mesh levels. GCI values of 2.1% and 3.8% respectively, both below the 5% threshold specified in the requirement document. Requirement document cites ASME V&V 40-2018 Annex B discretization error criteria without reference to the 2022 ASME V&V 20 supplement that revised GCI interpretation guidance for rotating machinery."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MRL 2 requires Gradation 2: test conditions documented and shown to be representative of COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions (fluid temperature 37°C, blood analog viscosity 3.5 mPa·s, inlet flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM) documented in test protocol TP-CPB-2024-03. Conditions span the COU operating envelope. Requirement document references ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 6.2 test condition fidelity criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MRL 2 requires Gradation 2: quantitative comparison metric between model outputs and experimental measurements for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index RH compared between CFD predictions and bench measurements at 5 operating points. Mean absolute percentage error of 8.7% with maximum deviation of 12.1%. All predicted RH values within experimental uncertainty bounds. Comparison methodology follows ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 6.4 as cited; the 2023 FDA guidance update on hemolysis model acceptance thresholds is not reflected in the requirement document binding."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MRL 2 requires Gradation 2: QoIs identified and justified as directly relevant to the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH computed from volume-averaged scalar stress and exposure time using a power-law hemolysis damage model. RH is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Secondary QoIs include peak shear stress magnitude and high-stress volume fraction. All QoIs are relevant to the worst-case hemolysis identification objective stated in the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "MRL 2 requires Gradation 2: validation activities performed on a system sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the same geometry used in the COU simulations. Operating conditions in validation experiments overlap with the COU operating envelope. Geometric similarity and operating condition overlap justify direct applicability of validation evidence to the COU per ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 6.1 relevance criteria."
    },
    {
