    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-accepted-2026q1",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2 as specified in ASME V&V 40-2018. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per Table 2 of the same standard. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD model predictions of relative hemolysis index within 12% of bench measurements across the full COU operating envelope. The governing requirement document binding ASME V&V 40-2018 is considered current and sufficient for this submission. The credibility assessment team concludes that the model is fit for the stated COU and the decision to accept the worst-case hemolysis operating point identification is supported by the available evidence.",
